s are the only event that brings the entire world together in peaceful competition.\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 828}, {\"ngram\": \"the only event\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 847}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire world\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 876}, {\"ngram\": \"peaceful competition\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then as now, the Olympic athletes are sending this powerful message: yes, it is possible to compete fiercely against each other and at the same time live peacefully together under one roof,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1110, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"this powerful message\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 978}, {\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1059}, {\"ngram\": \"one roof\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owing to cloudy weather, Greek actresses in the role of ancient priestesses used a flame lit in a rehearsal Monday in the 2,600-year-old Temple of Hera, near the stadium where the Olympics were born in 776 BC.\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1137, \"end\": 1142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999852280029377, \"rank\": 1.4729800540175895e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"score\": 0.9699953334164073, \"rank\": 0.030920521451565562, \"text\": \"BC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cloudy weather\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1135}, {\"ngram\": \"the role\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"ancient priestesse